### a. Owners' Equity for 2017 and 2018

Shareholders' equity is computed as follows:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Owners' Equity} &= \text{Total Assets} - {\text{Total Liabilities}}\\[1pt] 
\end{aligned}

Cash flow from assets is computed as follows:

$$\begin {array}{lrr} 
\text{Operating Cash Flow}&\$\hspace{10pt}\text{xx}\\ 
\text{Less: Change in Net Working Capital}&{\text{xx}}\\ 
\text{Less: Net Capital Spending}&\underline{\text{xx}}&\\ 
\textbf{Cash flow from assets}&\underline{\underline{\$\hspace{5pt}\textbf{xx}}}\\ \end{array}

Let's now compute for the operating cash flow as shown below:

$$\begin{aligned} 
\text{Operating Cash Flow} &= \text{EBIT} + {\text{Depreciation}} - {\text{Taxes}}\\[5pt] 
&= \text{\$6,803} + {\text{1,363}} - {\text{1,347}}\\[5pt] 
&= \underline{\underline{\text{\$6,819}}} 
\end{aligned}$$

Before we compute for the cash flow to creditors, we need to compute first the net new borrowings using the formula below:

 $$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Net New Borrowings} &= \text{Long-term debt 2018} - {\text{Long-term debt 2017}}\\[5pt]
&= \text{\$2,795} - {\text{2,628}}\\[5pt]
&= \underline{\underline{\text{\$167}}}
\end{aligned}$$
